JOHANNESBURG – An aircraft has crashed near the Wonderboom airport in Pretoria. Reports indicate that as many are 20 people are injured, one of them critically. Tshwane Metro Police Department spokesperson, Senior Superintendent Isaac Mahamba confirmed on Tuesday afternoon that a small plane crashed in the Kameeldrift plot. "We suspect that the plane was on its way to the Wonderboom airport," said Mahamba. "There is smoke all over and paramedics are on the scene. They will provide an update on any injuries." eNCA